title: Head on to the teahouse
unavailable-subtitle: You don't know the way yet
choose-if: know-way = 1 
tags: harbour, quay

You walk along the quay. With every step, the shouts and engine noises grow quieter. 

You reach a long pier with a small lighthouse at the end of it, its beam lost over the water. 

At the start of the pier, an old warehouse rises up. 

Paper lanterns sway in the wind. Between them, wind chimes made from old teapots clink softly together. 

Next to the warehouse, a drone hovers in place, dropping crumbs to a swarm of eager pigeons. Then it falters, tips over and lies twitching on the ground.

- #th_arrival

